   <mods:abstract>Littlepage contends that he has been economical. He has inherited money,
            and his resources do not principally come from his uncle and other friends. Jay was to
            act as Littlepage's friend and not as his banker. "Could my worthy uncle but know that
            for some inaccuracy in his letter I am at this moment reduced to sell my clothes for
            subsistence, what would be his feelings?" Gives his side of the argument surrounding his
            joining the Duke de Crillon. Includes an estimate of his expenses. Littlepage admits
            that he drew a bill without Jay's consent, but that was "because I had not time to know
            your sentiments."</mods:abstract>
